      "side": 1,
      "message": "Added the PID.\n\nThis check is safeguarding against buggy/racy behaviour in the client that causes it to request the wrong process (i.e. that Chrome accidentally asks for a dump of another program), but we can be confident that the request at least came from a registered client.\n\nThis is because the handle address in \"non_crash_information\" that we copy out of the client are transmitted at registration time, and we still have a valid HANDLE to the client process. So either we read from the right process, or the ReadProcessMemory() above would have failed, but there\u0027s nowhere for pid/HANDLE confusion to occur.",
